          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Secondary beams of (17-21)O ions were produced in a",
                "fragmentation reaction of a primary 40Ar beam",
                "delivered by the synchrotron SIS at GSI, Darmstadt.",
                "The secondary oxygen beams were separated in the",
                "fragment separator FRS operated at three different",
                "magnetic field settings optimized for (17,18)O,",
                " (19,20)O, and (21,22)O."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Natural carbon target (0.573 g/cm2)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detection system for the fragments",
                "consisted of two silicon detectors (one of them being",
                "position sensitive), a dipole magnet with a large",
                "gap of 0.5 m x 31.2 m, three scintillating fiber",
                "detectors, and a time-of-flight wall consisting of an",
                "array of 20 organic scintillation detectors, each one",
                "of 2000 x 100 x 10 mm3 size and placed about 11 m",
                "downstream from the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The main correction factor arises from the finite",
                "acceptance of the detector system for some of the",
                "fragments."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
